Wannabe Alchemist <br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uforgehammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Forgehammer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/28/02 11:37:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1464.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Twinking others is bad</span><hr size=1> This is my take on this. <br>
<br>
I give away stuff all the time. Hides if someone is doing tailoring. Food, just because I can. Non-Magical weapons. Just about all the junk I pick up that I don't have a need for. Any crafted items that are surplus.  I am more than happy to share. Especially with fellow barbarians. I have a fondness for my own kind. I think I would put a limit on magical items. I personally think acquiring a magical weapon, armor, spell is an acomplishment. I don't want anyone to hand me a magical weapon or armor I did not actually participate in the killing of or questing for. The only exception is TLC limited items that I have already gone over the limit to acquire. Then I am ready to pay hard cash for those items. <br>
     As far as Twinkers that have gifted equipment, I am indifferent to them. I feel somewhat miffed that they have better stuff than me at the level I am at, but I know I earned everything I have. That gives me pride in my character and his accomplishments. The game bottom line is about the person behind the screen. If they get more enjoyment out of getting more powerful items given to them, well then that is  their business. My game is all about accomplishing what I want the game to be for me. In my case, I am all about the quest. I do all the quest I can. So I feel good when I get a quest done.  The items I earn through the quest are the things I want to show off and use.  <br>
       So I don't mind if somebody examines me. I got all my stuff by &quot;sweat equity&quot;. Take a look. I may not impress anyone, but I feel good about Lasonta. <br>
<br>
Lasonta Barbarian Warrior<br>
